8.4 TERMINATION UPON SOLVENCY ISSUES. With mutual consent, either party shall have the right to dissolve or temporarily halt this Agreement upon providing written notice to the other party, effective immediately and without incurring any liability, under the following circumstances:

- The receiving party encounters a bankruptcy petition filed against it, or any proceeding or event having similar effect under any applicable law;
- The receiving party's assets are seized, attached, or otherwise disposed of under any legal process to satisfy a debt or obligation;
- The receiving party makes an assignment for the benefit of creditors or seeks protection under any bankruptcy, reorganization, readjustment of debts, arrangement, insolvency, or similar law.

This clause aims to safeguard both parties from potential financial instability or inability to fulfill contractual obligations due to the other party's solvency issues.
